==English==

===Adverb===
'''somehow'''
# In one way or another; in some way not yet known or designated; by some means; as, the thing must be done somehow; he lives somehow.
#: ''By their action upon one another they may be swelled '''somehow,''' so as to shorten the length.''  -Cheyne.
#: ''Although youngest of the familly, he has <u>'''somehow''' or other</u> got the entire management of all the others.''  -Sir W. Scott.

===Usage note===
The indefiniteness of somehow is emphasized by the addition of ''or other''.